rComments: Nuria is awesome! She can be tough but she really wants everyone to learn and is fair in her teaching.

WONDERFUL. Her accent is not a problem at all. She is exciting, funny, and adorable. Midterm and Final are in-class short essays, and are not a problem. Two papers as well, also not a problem. Reading is well selected and interesting. I love her and I would recommend her to anyone!

I am currently taking her Intro to Literary Genres, and she is GREAT! She teaches with such a passion, and its also great to see that she cares about the students. Although she lectures in spanish and has a thick spain accent, it doesn't matter, shes amazing, and even thought the reading is heavy, you learn a lot. She's awesome!

nuria is passionate about what she teaches and has a great sense of humor...but her class is kind of like reading a textbook.  and there is a TON of reading, although i did maybe 10% and got a B+.  class was dry but i learned mucho.

Professor Silleras-Fernandez is awesome! She is very helpful and always available for help. She has a thick accent, but the class her class is rewarding if the student pays attention and actively participates in class (section and completed reading). She assigned a lot of reading but highly recommended!
I loved her class. She is very knowledgeable and enthusiastic. I am currently taking her class now and I am enjoying it. Highly recommend her.

great professor!  really knows her stuff and is engaging.  a****-ton of reading, but you can sift through what is unecessary.  good amount of work well spread-out through the quarter.  take this class if youre interested in the period or just wanna fulfill a GE.

Nuria is a good teacher: very knowlegeable, helpful and clear. She's also a nice person and very understanding when things go wrong and willing to make accomidations if needed. I had fun in her class and learned a lot! (lots of work, but hey, it's History!)

Great class! A lot of reading and but you will learn so much about Spain! Nuria is such an enthusiastic and energetic lecturer and so caring about her students and what they have to say. She does have a thick accent but you will get used to it after a couple of days. A wonderful additon to the History Department at UCSC!
Great class!  Incredibly interesting selections of material, and very energetic lectures.  She is also very friendly and does have an accent but you will get used to it.
She's adorable and the material is fascinating. She's also really nice and approachable. Extra points for showing a clip of a Ken Russell film.

Nuria is really nice. shes from spain so her accent is pretty thick but she has really interesting lectures. she is always willing to talk to students about anything. but she is married to Prof. Brian Catlos, which is obvious in how much reading she hands out and the way her class in managed- so if you didnt like him u might not like her
